javax.xml.rpc.holders
Interface Holder

All Known Implementing Classes:
BigDecimalHolder, BigIntegerHolder, BooleanHolder, BooleanWrapperHolder, ByteArrayHolder, ByteHolder, ByteWrapperHolder, CalendarHolder, DataHandlerHolder, DateHolder, DayHolder, DoubleHolder, DoubleWrapperHolder, DurationHolder, FloatHolder, FloatWrapperHolder, HexBinaryHolder, ImageHolder, IntegerWrapperHolder, IntHolder, LongHolder, LongWrapperHolder, MimeMultipartHolder, MonthDayHolder, MonthHolder, NegativeIntegerHolder, NonNegativeIntegerHolder, NonPositiveIntegerHolder, NormalizedStringHolder, ObjectHolder, OctetStreamHolder, PositiveIntegerHolder, QNameHolder, SchemaHolder, ShortHolder, ShortWrapperHolder, SourceHolder, StringHolder, TimeHolder, TokenHolder, UnsignedByteHolder, UnsignedIntHolder, UnsignedLongHolder, UnsignedShortHolder, URIHolder, YearHolder, YearMonthHolder
public interface Holder

The java.xml.rpc.holders.Holder interface represents the base interface for both standard and generated Holder classes. A generated Holder class is required to implement this Holder interface.

Version:
1.0
